                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On April 17, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MGC2">McGhee</persName> submitted a
                    memorandum to the Secretary suggesting action on a program of economic aid to
                    the Near East (see <ref target="#pg_642">page 642</ref>). This memorandum was in
                    light of a request from the Government of Israel for a fiscal year 1952 grant of
                    $150 million, which had generated a great deal of discussion within the United
                    States Government. For documentation regarding the Israeli request <pb
                        facs="0151" n="111" xml:id="pg_111"/> and United States reaction to it
                    through the end of April, see <ref target="#pg_559">pages 559</ref> ff.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
